OL,3,CScottish election: SNP predicted fifth
OL,4,Cconsecutive win
OL,6,FIn the last Scottish election, the SNP
OL,7,Funder former First Minister Nicola
OL,8,FSturgeon, secured 64 seats, one more
OL,9,Fthan the previous election but one
OL,10,Fshort of the 65 seats needed for a
OL,11,Ffull majority.
OL,13,FSince 2016, Scottish Labour, which
OL,14,Fused to have strong control of
OL,15,FScotland, has enjoyed third place,
OL,16,Fsitting behind the Scottish
OL,17,FConservatives.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1778371373
OL,3,CScottish election: SNP predicted fifth
OL,4,Cconsecutive win
OL,6,FThe same final poll from YouGov that
OL,7,Fpredicted a victory for the SNP also
OL,8,Fpredicted a collapse for the
OL,9,FConservatives, with a fight for the
OL,10,Fremaining places a close call between
OL,11,FReform, Labour, and the Greens.
OL,13,FWe won't know about the first results
OL,14,Ffrom Glasgow until roughly 2.30 pm,
OL,15,Fbut polling suggests this usually safe
OL,16,Fhome for the SNP could be under threat
OL,17,Ffrom the Greens, who have seen a
OL,18,Fdramatic rise in popularity under
OL,19,Ftheir new national leader, Zack
OL,20,FPolanski, and Scottish co-leaders Ross
OL,21,FGreer and Gillian Mackay.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
